### Per-App Content

```typescript
// apps/docs/content/docs/
// apps/www/content/blog/
// apps/dashboard/content/dashboard/
```

Each app has own content directory:
- **apps/docs**: `/docs/*` documentation
- **apps/www**: `/blog/*` blog posts
- **apps/dashboard**: `/` and other MDX pages (content/dashboard/)

### Dashboard App MDX Routing

The dashboard app uses a specific pattern for MDX routing:

```typescript
// Root route handles index.mdx
app/(dashboard)/page.tsx
  → dashboardSource.getPage([])
  → content/dashboard/index.mdx

// Required catch-all handles other MDX files
app/(dashboard)/[...slug]/page.tsx
  → dashboardSource.getPage(['context'])
  → content/dashboard/context.mdx
```

**Important:**
- Use **required catch-all** `[...slug]` not optional `[[...slug]]` to avoid conflicts with root route
- Both routes must be in the same route group `(dashboard)` to inherit layout
- Root route uses `getPage([])` for index.mdx
- Catch-all route uses `getPage(params.slug)` for other MDX files
- See routing.mdc for complete pattern details

